The paper deals with lossy distributed compression of correlated sources, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of multi-layer codebooks and the analysis of achievable regions also suggest that the paper could be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves distributed processing of information sources, which could be relevant to the distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the use of random codes and the analysis of information measures suggest that the paper could also be relevant to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
